version: 0.9.1
- UI Settings Pass (every Wave 1/2 + 0.7.2 backend setting now manageable from the UI)
  - moral-settings: four new sections — Emotional Decay, Forgiveness, Emotional Scars (FormArray CRUD for triggers: intents/tones/keywords/persistence_floor/intensity_boost), Inner Voice — plus a llama.cpp provider block (active-provider option + fallback checkbox).
  - rag-settings: Memory Consolidation section (importance threshold + LLM judge with provider select Ollama/llama.cpp and model select fed from the shared Ollama model pool) and Narrative Diary section (enabled/min_chars/max_chars). Saved via a separate `{memory: ...}` PATCH payload with its own dirty-snapshot.
  - compliance-settings: new main-modal tab with five sections — Validator, Language guard, Confidence, Factuality, Self-Watcher. All checkboxes via `app-ui-checkbox`; multi-key PATCH body (validator/language_guard/confidence/factuality/self_watcher).
  - analyzer-settings: llama.cpp provider (enabled/base_url/model/temperature/max_tokens/request_timeout) + fallback option, normalizing `llama_cpp` <-> `llamaCpp` key shapes on load.
  - voice-settings: Qwen3-TTS module block (model_name, device, dtype, max_seq_len, language, temperature, top_k, repetition_penalty, max_new_tokens, do_sample).
  - audio-settings: STT block — default language, auto-detect, provider select (faster-whisper / sherpa-onnx) and conditional sherpa fields per model_type (transducer/paraformer/whisper/moonshine) with paths relative to STT_MODELS_DIR.
  - system-settings: audit_logs retention editor (per-severity age_days + hard_cap grids), read-only MODE env info block, and a split between "UI language (system.language)" and "Generation language (User.language)" with explanatory hints.
- User Language Endpoint
  - Added `PATCH /api/auth/me/settings` and `auth.update_user_settings(user_uuid, language, timezone)` so the generation-language source of truth (`UserSettings.language`, consumed by `resolve_user_language`) is editable from the UI. Frontend: `AuthService.updateMeSettings$()` keeps the cached user in sync.
- Frontend Config Infrastructure
  - Extended `project-config.{dto,model}.ts` with ~20 interfaces covering moral decay/forgiveness/scars/inner_voice, memory consolidation + diary.narrative, validator, language_guard, confidence, factuality, self_watcher, audit_logs.retention, and stt/sherpa_onnx.
  - New mappers `compliance-config-mapper.ts`, `audit-logs-config-mapper.ts`, `stt-config-mapper.ts`; extended moral/memory mappers; `config.service.ts` PATCH whitelist gained seven new top-level keys.
  - Locales (ru-RU/en-US): new blocks `complianceSettings`, `ragSettings`, `voiceSettings`, `audioSettings`, `systemSettings`, extended `moralSettings`, sidebar tab `compliance`.

version: 0.9.0
- Audit Logs in DB (replaces JSONL as the primary store)
  - New `audit_logs` table; `log_audit_entry` writes DB-first with a JSONL fallback for the boot window before initialize. `get_debug_log()` reads DB-first with JSONL fallback, preserving None-for-404 semantics.
  - `MODE` env var (read before initialize, hence env not DB-config): `dev` (default) writes everything, `prod` drops info/success severities.
  - Nightly per-severity retention (`prune_audit_logs`): age_days (debug/info 7d, warning 30d, error/audit_fail 90d) + hard caps (info 50K, warning 10K, error 5K). Config: `audit_logs.retention.*`.
- Validator (LLM-as-judge output compliance)
  - New `modules/validator/`: `validate_output(output, instructions)` scores compliance 0-1 against instructor directives via the active generation provider. Never raises — any failure returns `skipped=True`. Prompt: `VALIDATOR_COMPLIANCE_PROMPT` (strict JSON).
  - Wired into sync `generate_standard` via `_maybe_run_validator`; compliance below `validator.threshold` writes a DebugVault entry (`kind=validation_failed`). Auto-reroll deferred to a follow-up.
- DebugVault (curated anomaly store)
  - New `debug_vault_entries` table + `modules/debug_vault/` (insert/list/get/mark_reviewed) + REST (`GET /api/debug_vault`, `GET /{id}`, `POST /{id}/review`).
  - Every vault write mirrors an `audit_logs` row (`event_type=debug_vault_entry_recorded`, `details.vault_entry_id`) for cross-lookup.
- Language Guard
  - New `modules/language_guard/`: CPU-only unicode-script counter (8 script buckets, no external deps). Compares output's dominant script against `User.language`; mixed-language outputs below `min_dominance` are skipped as legitimate code-switching. Mismatch writes DebugVault (`kind=language_mismatch`).
  - New canonical resolver `modules.system.user.resolve_user_language(user_uuid, character_id, fallback)`: UserSettings.language -> system.language -> static. Diary and moral inner-voice migrated onto it (fixes the inner_voice fallback that wrongly used system.language).
- Confidence Estimation
  - New `modules/confidence/`: one mini LLM call scoring 0-1 whether the output addressed the user message. Score persists on `History.runtime_meta.confidence` (+threshold +low flag). Low confidence logs WARNING — deliberately NOT DebugVault (signal, not anomaly).
  - `update_history_runtime_meta` gained `merge: bool = False` for shallow-merge partial updates that keep upstream metadata intact.
- Factuality Check
  - New `modules/factuality/`: regex claim extractor (years, dates, numbers+units latin/cyrillic, capitalized phrases with sentence-initial drop) + lorebook lookup per claim. Gated on `confidence_low` by default. No web access — local memory only. Result persists on `runtime_meta.factuality = {supported, sources_found, claims}`; output text is never modified.
- Self-Watcher / Meta-cognition
  - New `expectation_events` table + `modules/self_watcher/`: per-turn comparison of PAI's predicted emotion (stamped on the previous assistant message's runtime_meta from moral_state) vs the user's actual analyzer tone. Valence classifier (RU/EN) + mismatch scorer; rows recorded above `mismatch_threshold`.
  - Nightly reflection: LLM clusters recent events into 2-4 first-person sentences written to `daily_activity_diary.payload.self_reflection` (wired into loop_initiative after audit retention). Observation-only — never influences the current turn.
- Narrative Diary
  - The daily diary LLM call now returns an extra `narrative` field (200-400 words, first person, in the user's language) in the same JSON pass — no second LLM call. Stored top-level at `payload.narrative` with configurable min/max chars; rendered in `features/diary` as an italic lead block.
  - Removed "LIM" from all system prompts and module docstrings (PAI is the system identity; LIM remains character data only). Dead commented-out code dropped from loop_initiative.
- Scope Decision
  - Skill Training pipeline (+SkillConnector/Injector/Collector), DAMP, and MetaLIM are explicitly OUT of the core build. No web-fallback in the hot path anywhere.
- Tests: 111 new across the wave (audit logs db/reader/retention, validator + integration, debug vault, language guard, confidence, factuality, narrative diary, self-watcher). Regressions: 0.

version: 0.8.0
- Emotional Core (Wave 1)
  - Emotional decay: `EmotionalTrace` gained `decay_rate`, `persistence_floor`, `resolved`, `last_decayed_at`; nightly idempotent decay job in loop_initiative (`moral.decay.{enabled, global_rate}`).
  - Forgiveness: new `forgiveness_events` table + analyzer-tone heuristic (`moral.forgiveness.*`) — compensating user behaviour softens old negative traces, never below `persistence_floor`.
  - Emotional scars: `moral.scars.triggers[]` (intents/tones/keywords) create traces with elevated `persistence_floor` + intensity boost; first matching trigger wins.
  - Inner voice: one short first-person sentence per turn explaining the current feeling (`moral.inner_voice.*`), persisted in trace notes and surfaced via `result.meta.inner_voice` on the WS moral_state event.
- Tests: test_emotional_decay, test_forgiveness, test_emotional_scars, test_inner_voice.

version: 0.7.2
- Tunnel-Aware API Access Guard
  - Replaced the implicit "CORS *" policy with a positive access check in `core/access_guard.py`, ordered inside the request logger so 403 rejections still show up in console logs.
  - Added `system.api_access_mode` DB key with three values: `tunnel_aware` (default, loopback + currently active tunnel `public_url`), `strict_local` (loopback only, even when a tunnel is running), `open` (legacy permissive behaviour for development).
  - Added `modules.system.tunnel.runtime_snapshot()` returning `{running, public_url}` without the DB roundtrip that `get_status()` does, so the hot-path middleware stays cheap.
  - WebSocket handshakes are gated via `core.access_guard.accept_ws()` at the top of `/api/ws`.
- llama.cpp Provider Parity
  - Added the llama.cpp transport (`modules/llama_cpp/`) with sync + async streaming chat completions, embeddings, and process-launcher helpers for `llama-server`. Multi-GPU profiles are honoured; single-CUDA profiles get `CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES` scoping.
  - Registered llama.cpp adapters in every existing provider registry: generative (`modules/generative/providers/llama_cpp.py`), analyzer, moral matrix, vision (`llama_cpp_vision` via `--mmproj`). Each domain keeps its own `active_provider` + `providers.<name>.model` selection — no new "service model" abstraction.
  - All adapters are off by default. Opt in per-domain via `<module>.providers.llama_cpp.enabled = true` and `base_url`.
  - Sampler config (temperature/top_p/top_k/min_p/repeat_penalty/max_tokens) merges DB defaults with per-request options; `num_predict` is aliased to `max_tokens` for parity with the Ollama provider's request shape.
- sherpa-onnx STT
  - Added `stt.provider` switch: `whisper` (default, existing faster-whisper) or `sherpa_onnx`. Whisper path is untouched.
  - New `modules/voice/sherpa_onnx_engine.py` supports all four OfflineRecognizer families (transducer, paraformer, whisper, moonshine) with fingerprint-based recognizer caching.
  - Relative paths in `stt.sherpa_onnx.*` resolve against `STT_MODELS_DIR` (`backend/storage/models/stt`), the same gitignored model storage faster-whisper already uses; absolute paths pass through.
  - Added `sherpa-onnx>=1.13.0` to `backend/requirements.txt`.
- Qwen-TTS
  - Added `QwenTTSProvider` via `faster-qwen3-tts` next to Coqui/Edge/ElevenLabs/gTTS/Offline in the existing TTSManager registry. In-process, lazy load, shutdown releases GPU.
  - Weights download via HuggingFace Hub on first synth and pin to `TTS_MODELS_DIR/qwen` (gitignored). `HF_HOME` is only set when not already in env.
  - DB config: `voice.voice_modules.qwen.*` with load-time fields (`model_name/device/dtype/max_seq_len`) and sampling tunables. Selectable as `voice.active_module = "qwen"`. Default remains `edge`.
  - Added `faster-qwen3-tts>=0.2.6` to `backend/requirements.txt`.
- Shutdown Hook
  - Wired `core.initialize.shutdown_services()` to `main.app_shutdown` — previously the function existed but was never invoked, so vision/TTS/LLM provider weights only got cleaned up implicitly on process exit.
  - Extended `shutdown_services()` to release every registered generation provider (regardless of `model_memory_profile`), shut down the TTS subsystem, and stop the vision service. Each step is isolated with try/except so one bridge failing cannot block the model-release path.
  - Does NOT touch the existing `should_release_resources` / `model_memory_profile` policy — those continue to control per-use behaviour as before.
- Memory Consolidation Policy
  - Sleep consolidation now consults the LLM-generated `importance_score` that `_summarize_activity` already returns. Entries below `memory.consolidation.importance_threshold` (default 0.2) are flagged `payload.pruned = {reason: low_importance, score, threshold, at}` and hidden from default reads.
  - `list_daily_activity_entries` gained `include_pruned: bool = False`, so RAG/context consumers automatically skip pruned entries; admin views opt in.
  - Threshold=0.0 disables the filter (kill switch); lowering the threshold un-prunes existing `low_importance` flags so policy reversals do not require manual DB edits.
  - Added optional contradiction-resolver judge (`memory.consolidation.judge.enabled`, off by default). When enabled and `_summarize_activity` returned non-empty contradictions, one LLM call per entry (Ollama or llama.cpp) maps each contradiction note to a recent entry plus an action: `supersede` (mark older entry `pruned.reason = superseded_by` in a second pass), `merge` (back-link in `payload.merged_from`), `keep_both`, or `skip`. Nothing fires on a chat turn — only during nightly sleep consolidation.
  - The judge response is parsed via `_parse_judge_response`, which tolerates JSON-in-prose and code fences and drops invalid actions; unknown `entry_id` is a safe no-op; `supersede` never stomps on non-`low_importance` pruned markers (e.g. `user_archived`).
- Reliability & Regression Safety
  - Added regression coverage around the access guard (all three modes, tunnel on/off, WS handshake), llama.cpp transport + provider behaviour, sherpa-onnx routing, Qwen-TTS lifecycle, llama.cpp vision adapter, and diary consolidation (importance pruning + judge resolver). Baseline 66 → 154 passing regression tests; the 5 pre-existing `synthesis_*` failures are unrelated to this branch and tracked separately.

version: 0.7.1
- Unified Media/Image Pipeline
  - Added a shared media image pipeline used by Sandbox, Synthesis, main chat image generation, and Telegram image flows.
  - Added LLM prompt-builder tracing for image generation: tool context, generated prompt, negative prompt, provider route, parameters, result media, and review/vision metadata.
  - Improved image prompt building so raw system strings such as dates, clock labels, and emotion labels are converted into visual composition cues instead of being copied into prompts.
  - Removed fixed `systemOutfit` from image prompt context so generated scenes can improvise clothing from intent, setting, time, and mood.
  - `emotionMood` is now included only when Moral Matrix is enabled and has an actual emotion state.
- ComfyUI & Synthesis
  - Added ComfyUI provider integration with checkpoint discovery, endpoint/resource inspection, and txt2img generation.
  - Added ComfyUI-aware generation parameters: width, height, steps, CFG, sampler, scheduler, checkpoint, seed.
  - Split `sampler` and `scheduler` in Synthesis and Sandbox UI/API payloads so values such as `euler` are sent as sampler, not scheduler.
  - Synthesis and Sandbox now use provider-level ComfyUI defaults instead of overwriting them with stale local UI defaults.
  - Added temporary-output persistence control for Sandbox and Synthesis; generated image output storage is ignored by git.
- Sandbox
  - Added an image pipeline mode that shows the generated prompt, input tool context, generation route, parameters, traces, and output image.
  - Added a dedicated Vision mode for describing input images/screen context without accidentally launching image generation.
  - Fixed Sandbox layout so panels remain pinned and scrolling is contained inside the controls/chat/process areas.
  - Added provider/model loading for image generation, including ComfyUI checkpoint selection.
- Telegram
  - Telegram generation is forced through synchronous generation paths outside main chat streaming behavior.
  - Routed Telegram image command, `take_photo`, and test-image flows through the shared media pipeline.
  - Telegram test images now generate meaningful captions from image review/vision context instead of sending generic test text.
  - Added fast repeat-recovery path that reuses already built context/tool outputs, disables thinking, and avoids rerunning the full Decision Layer pipeline when repeat guard blocks a reply.
  - Fixed duplicate current-user messages in Telegram payloads by deduplicating recent history before formatting model input.
  - Added adjacent duplicate suppression for repeated assistant/user history rows before sending context to the model.
- Chat Runtime & Streaming
  - Fixed duplicate live-status rendering in main chat by hiding the global loading indicator once a streaming assistant message has its own runtime status.
  - Fixed reasoning/status overlap by hiding closed `<think>` blocks during live final-answer streaming while preserving completed reasoning display afterward.
  - Added longer Ollama stream read timeout handling and converted stream stalls into structured provider errors instead of raw aiohttp tracebacks.
  - WebSocket generation errors now emit `run_status=error` and `typing_end` so the UI does not remain stuck in a running state.
- UI & Library Polish
  - Replaced several ad-hoc checkbox controls with project UI checkboxes.
  - Updated Library and Sidebar icon/preview controls, including books/library icon treatment and file preview action cleanup.
  - Added empty-state text for chat history and memory storage blocks.
- Reliability & Regression Safety
  - Added/updated regression coverage around Telegram generation mode, empty-content recovery, streaming reasoning state, Ollama client behavior, input envelope handling, synthesis routes, and Sandbox/media flows.
  - Hardened config/auth/runtime cleanup behavior and provider error reporting across the affected generation paths.

version: 0.7
- Telegram Notification-Driven Runtime
  - Reworked Telegram bridge to notification-first processing (event → normalized notification → sequential worker) for safer autonomous behavior.
  - Hardened write safety with sender-level final gate and deny-by-default policy for public chats/channels.
  - Added private-only public reflection delivery flow (read public source, deliver reflection to configured private target).
  - Extended Telegram runtime observability with outbound target diagnostics and policy-aware audit events.
- Social/Telegram UI & Policy Controls
  - Expanded Social Settings with reflection targeting, source selection, quiet hours, initiative cadence, autonomous inbox, and tool orchestration controls.
  - Added chat catalog-based selection flows to reduce manual chat_id setup and improve operator safety.
  - Improved localization coverage and helper text for Telegram/social sections.
- Generation & Visual Self-Expression
  - Added UI-first visual profile pipeline (composer + deterministic prompt builder + profile/history helpers) for stateful image expression.
  - Integrated visual intent into synthesis and Telegram test-image path.
  - Added stricter image send handling/retries for Telegram delivery path.
- Vision Provider Layer
  - Added configurable `ollama_vision` provider support in the vision module.
  - Added provider capability probe/status endpoint and Vision UI status panel (`configured/supported/unavailable`) with manual support check.
  - Added Ollama model list integration in Vision UI for provider model selection.
  - Improved Ollama vision error surfacing (HTTP/body diagnostics) and lightweight probe options.
- Diary/Memory/Context Quality
  - Continued separation of runtime action logs vs semantic context for model inputs.
  - Stabilized diary/memory-facing runtime traces and message flow constraints in Telegram-related paths.
- Stability & Regression Safety
  - Added/updated Telegram pipeline regression tests and synthesis/vision-related validations.
  - Fixed startup regression in vision initialization (`VisionService` bootstrap scope/import ordering).
  - Fixed UI refresh stalls in settings screens by tightening async update + change-detection behavior.

version: 0.6
- Platform & Architecture
  - Introduced module-oriented boundaries: moved legacy core domain logic into dedicated modules (`memory`, `moral_matrix`, `vision`, `system`) and kept `core` focused on orchestration/startup.
  - Added `SystemModule` facade (`backend/modules/system/service.py`) for config/runtime access and cross-module safe calls.
  - Added interaction policy layer (`backend/services/interaction_policy.py`) to enforce role-based capabilities for history/memory/edit/reroll actions.
- Auth, Session & Bootstrap
  - Added full auth flow (register/login/refresh/logout, guards/interceptor on frontend, auth routes/services on backend).
  - First registration now provisions `owner`; subsequent registrations default to `user`.
  - Startup pipeline stabilized: backend readiness-first launch flow (`run.py`), safer startup checks, schema bootstrap ordering, and DB-first config compatibility.
- DB-first Config & Character Management
  - Migrated to DB-first config access with split settings tables (`user_configs`, `user_tts_settings`, `user_vision_settings`) and runtime-safe wrappers.
  - Added character catalog endpoints and YAML import flow in system config routes.
  - Introduced active character model in `user_settings.active_character_id` and switched runtime routing/history loading to active-character resolution.
  - Added fallback/backfill logic: if active character is missing, resolve from latest history and persist to `user_settings`.
- Chat & Realtime Reliability
  - WebSocket pipeline hardened: run IDs, stop semantics, runtime trace streaming, better send safety, and richer error signaling.
  - Fixed reconnect/empty-state behavior in frontend chat and improved WS client robustness against transient disconnects.
  - Added per-run metadata persistence into history runtime fields (provider/model/usage/traces/timing).
- Memory & Moral Matrix
  - Added memory emulator route/workflow for staged retrieval inspection and debugging.
  - Expanded memory knowledge layer (`anchors`, `associations`) and owner-scoped access controls.
  - Moral Matrix route/provider path stabilized with safer character resolution and degraded-response fallback in failure scenarios.
- Voice/TTS/RVC
  - Voice settings UI was expanded with provider-aware controls and integrated RVC/XTTS related backend hooks.
  - Added RVC runtime assets/pipeline files and bootstrap services for model status/download/import flows.
  - Refactored TTS manager/service contracts to centralize provider selection, preview generation, and safer playback lifecycle.
- Synthesis (Image Generation)
  - Added synthesis module and routes with pluggable providers.
  - Introduced `Z-Image-Turbo` provider and a generic Diffusers provider path for local model-driven generation.
- Frontend Platform Upgrade
  - Added new feature modules/pages (`auth`, `memory`, `matrix`, `synthesis`, `audit`, `diary`) and expanded routing guards.
  - Introduced shared UI-kit components (`ui-button`, `ui-input`, `ui-select`, `ui-range`, `ui-checkbox`, `ui-textarea`, etc.) and unified icon registry/assets.
  - Updated config mappers/services for new backend schema and module settings.
- Storage & Paths
  - Consolidated model storage layout under `backend/storage/models/*` domains (vision, rvc, etc.) and aligned path constants.
  - Added/updated helper services for XTTS/RVC resources and model path resolution.
- Dependency & Runtime Notes
  - Updated `backend/requirements.txt` and frontend package set to support new auth/synthesis/TTS/UI capabilities.
  - Added/kept warnings/telemetry handling improvements (including optional runtime hardening for noisy libs on clean builds).

version: 0.5
- Localization & Logging
  - Added a `.env`-driven localization service with EN/RU dictionaries, automatic fallbacks, and cached lookups for backend modules.
  - Extended the logger to resolve localized strings, persist message keys/args, capture active language, and mirror localized output to the console.
  - Updated analyzer, memory, audio, voice, TTS, vision, and initialization flows to emit localized audit events with contextual parameters.
- Voice, TTS & Vision
  - Localized the entire VAD listener pipeline (startup, trigger handling, duplicate suppression) and audio playback threads with structured console prints.
  - ElevenLabs and offline TTS providers now report localized progress/errors, chunk counts, and synthesis timings; audio playback interruptions are localized per device.
  - Vision service, worker, and AppleVision provider log localized monitor/window selection, YOLO/SSIM metrics, capture errors, and inference lifecycle events.
- Memory & API
  - Memory routes and short-term memory helpers now output localized schema checks, refresh steps, and retrieval logs.
  - Analyzer provider manager and other backend utilities adopt the localization service for consistent RU/EN messaging across the stack.
- Backend & Core Systems
  - Introduced a `.env`-driven localization service with EN/RU dictionaries, cached loading, and fallback logic; wired it into the logger so every audit entry prints translated text with contextual parameters.
  - Added the Moral Matrix module (repository, heuristics, Ollama/OpenRouter providers with fallback manager) and hooked its evaluation results into the decision layer.
  - Rebuilt the high-level generation pipeline (`modules/generative/conversation.py`) to orchestrate streaming providers, sanitise attachments, split reasoning `<think>` blocks, and persist richer metadata in storage/history.
  - Expanded default configuration, DTOs, and routes with moral/analyzer/generation fields, plus helpers for PATCH updates and system prompt management.
- Voice & Audio Pipeline
  - Overhauled the TTS manager with provider retry/back-off, queue/worker controls, self-trigger protection, and detailed logging across Edge, ElevenLabs, gTTS, and offline fallbacks.
  - Localised the VAD listener (startup, trigger handling, duplicate suppression) and audio playback threads; console prints now mirror audit events with translated strings.
  - ElevenLabs and offline providers report download progress, synthesis timings, and error states via the localization layer; audio playback interruptions include per-device context.
- Vision & Memory
  - Vision service/worker emit localized diagnostics for monitor/window selection, YOLO counts, SSIM/optical-flow metrics, and capture failures; AppleVision provider logs localized load/ready/inference lifecycle messages.
  - Short-term memory schema checks, refresh routines, and analyzer provider fallbacks now surface localized console/audit output.
- Frontend & Tooling
  - Updated Angular config service/mappers to handle partial updates for new sections (moral, analyzer, system prompt) and aligned UI logging with backend schema changes.
  - Added RU/EN translation assets and localization helpers so the frontend mirrors backend language selection during diagnostics.
- Bugfix & Stability Improvements
  - Voice & TTS
    - Edge-TTS provider now checks service availability before fetching voices; if the service is unreachable, voices are skipped and not loaded into the frontend (8-second timeout threshold).
    - Added configuration flag for selecting offline TTS mode directly from the Audio settings.
  - Configuration & Visual Module
    - Fixed monitor selection and value assignment issues affecting the Vision module.
    - Restored proper handling of character name and owner name fields in configuration.
    - Fixed analyzer settings not applying correctly after updates.
    - Resolved an issue where Audio settings overwrote unrelated config sections on save.
    - Improved visual provider initialization and parameter mapping for stability.

version: 0.4
- Backend & LLM orchestration
  - Introduced modular analyzer and generative packages with provider managers that fail over between OpenRouter and Ollama, plus shared Ollama client helpers for text and vision chats.
  - Rewired generation streaming and synchronous paths through the new providers, centralizing error handling and audit logging around the fallback chain.
- Memory & Storage
  - Added a MemoryModule that can collect recent/session context via embeddings, integrate lorebook lookups, and report retrieval metadata.
  - Implemented a storage service + /api/media route to persist message attachments on disk, auto-upgrade the storage schema, and expose safe downloads.
- Config & API surface
  - Expanded config models, DTOs, and routes to cover analyzer, generator, memory, and media settings; refreshed mappers on both backend and frontend to keep camelCase ↔ snake_case conversions in sync.
  - Updated vector/service helpers and new storage endpoints to cooperate with the modular services.
- Voice & TTS
  - Added a gTTS provider with automatic pyttsx3 fallback, expanded audit logging, and folded it into the provider sequence so fallback order is ElevenLabs → gTTS → offline.
  - Reworked the TTS stop pipeline to raise the interrupt flag, clear the playback queue, and leave the worker thread ready for future jobs, fixing cases where new chunks were still spoken after Stop.
- Decision & diagnostics
  - DecisionLayer now delegates to the shared TTS service, emits richer analyzer/vision logs, and keeps the troubleshooting prints inline with the new modules.
- Resources
  - Added a configurable timeout (default 8s) to `/api/resources/voices` so the UI fails fast when the remote voice provider hangs.
- Frontend
  - Added analyzer settings modal, analyzer/memory config mappers, and expanded settings UI to surface provider selection, fallbacks, and new API fields.
  - Synced chat/settings components with the backend schema so media, analyzer, and memory options stay editable from the UI.


version: 0.3
- Config & Backend
  - Moved the default config into constants/default_config.py, expanded it with system/core sections, voice module settings, STT defaults, and snake_case audio/vision keys.
  - Config service now logs recursive updates, exposes set_config_value, validates user_id, and config routes can read/write system prompts while history fetch supports offsets.
- Voice & Conversation
  - Introduced a shared voice_state controller and wired it through VAD, streaming, and TTS so listening/waiting/speaking stages stay in sync.
  - Added ElevenLabs TTS integration with per-module settings, sanitized streamed speech (# removal, emoji stripping), and skipped synthesis when voice is disabled.
  - VAD listener now deduplicates transcripts, honours the new trigger bypass flag, normalizes config keys, and guards processing with async locks to block self-trigger loops.
- Vision
  - Added an Apple FastVLM provider and structured provider configs, including capture metadata in summaries and optional frame dumps controlled via config.
  - Capture worker now supports monitor/window modes, clamps invalid monitor indices, and reports when the active window falls outside the capture region.
- Frontend & Settings
  - Refactored config mappers into domain utilities aligned with the backend schema and renamed the API client method to updateConfig$.
  - Added Core/System settings views (system prompt editor, theme/language switches, cognitive analyzer controls) and new ConfigService helpers for system endpoints.
  - Theme service now persists the selected theme and initializes stored preferences.
- UI & Components
  - Introduced notification and skeleton shared components plus an emoji picker with a data generation script and bundled emoji dataset.
  - Refreshed chat/settings/layout styles and tabs to surface the new settings groups and debug affordances.


version: 0.2
- Backend
  - Broke out reusable config/constants modules (rules, prompts, paths, indicators, errors, visual, etc.) and updated initialization to preload them.
  - Extracted the vision stack into `backend/modules/vision` with dedicated service/analyzer/worker, refreshed moral & cognitive analyzers and initialization hooks.
  - Introduced `backend/modules/voice` with an async VAD listener, configurable wake words, REST controls (`/api/voice/mode/*`) and safe stubs in `voice_service`.
  - Persisted LLM reasoning in a new `reasoning` table; FastAPI history responses now merge `<think>…</think>` back into message content, and deletions cascade to reasoning rows.
  - Adjusted instructor/API pipeline: vision context is appended via `[CONTEXT:VISUAL]` plus explicit `[INSTRUCTION]` cues so models reliably use screen data.
  - Updated lorebook/RAG services, config service, database helpers, and run loop wiring to match the new module layout.
  - Refreshed backend requirements (added `webrtcvad`, vision OCR/YOLO deps), committed `requirements.lock`, and shipped a CUDA 12.1 torch manifest.

- Frontend
  - Introduced a reusable `message-renderer` module (markdown pipes, text/code/thinking blocks) and rewired chat UI to use it.
  - Restyled chat/history components, lorebook modals, websocket service, and mocks to support thinking blocks and richer formatting.
  - Added project-level `package.json`/`package-lock.json`, bundled `marked` + typings, and updated build tooling/run script to start both frontend and backend.

- Voice & Logging
  - Added detailed VAD logging (trigger hits/misses, self-trigger detection), trigger-word configuration via config, and ensured async scheduling works from PortAudio callbacks.
  - Created REST endpoints to start/stop/status VoiceMode, wired WebSocket stubs, and ensured STT segments flow through the decision layer only when triggers fire.

- UX polish
  - Redesigned the thinking block with LIM palette, accordion-style expand/collapse, and auto-collapse after streaming.
  - Ensured reasoning removal on history deletion and tightened audit logs around VAD, visual context, and API generation flows.


